---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="10 Extreme Couponing Tips for Maximum Savings">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    {/* Hero Section */}
    <div class="relative mb-8 sm:mb-12">
      <img 
        src="/images/blog/extreme-couponing.jpg"
        alt="Extreme Couponing Tips"
        class="w-full h-[300px] sm:h-[500px] object-cover rounded-lg sm:rounded-xl shadow-lg"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/60 to-transparent rounded-lg sm:rounded-xl"></div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-4 sm:p-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-2 sm:mb-4 leading-tight">
          10 Extreme Couponing Tips for Maximum Savings
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-200 text-base sm:text-lg mb-2">Published on December 9, 2024</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Article Content */}
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      {/* Introduction */}
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6 sm:mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Ready to take your savings to the next level? Extreme couponing isn't just about clipping a few coupons—it's a strategic approach to maximizing your savings on every purchase.
      </p>

      {/* Main Content Sections */}
      <div class="space-y-8 sm:space-y-12">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            1. Create a Coupon Organization System
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            The foundation of successful extreme couponing is organization. Use a binder with clear plastic sleeves to organize coupons by category and expiration date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            2. Learn Store Policies Inside Out
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Each store has its own coupon policy. Know which stores:
          </p>
          <ul class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Allow coupon stacking</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Accept competitor coupons</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Offer price matching</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Double or triple coupons</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            3. Master the Art of Stacking
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Combine manufacturer coupons with:
          </p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Coupon Types</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                  <span>Store coupons</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                  <span>Rebate apps</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Additional Savings</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                  <span>Store rewards</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                  <span>Sales promotions</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            4. Time Your Shopping Right
          </h2>
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/5 to-primary/10 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-8">
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center text-primary mr-3">1</span>
                <span>Shop during off-peak hours for better service</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center text-primary mr-3">2</span>
                <span>Take advantage of double coupon days</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center text-primary mr-3">3</span>
                <span>Plan around store sales cycles</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center text-primary mr-3">4</span>
                <span>Shop seasonal clearance events</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            5. Build Your Stockpile Strategically
          </h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white shadow-sm rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 border border-gray-100">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 sm:mb-3">Storage Space</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base">Designate a specific area for your stockpile</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white shadow-sm rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 border border-gray-100">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 sm:mb-3">Inventory System</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base">Track expiration dates and quantities</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white shadow-sm rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 border border-gray-100">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 sm:mb-3">Rotation</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base">Use FIFO (First In, First Out) method</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            6. Build a Stockpile Strategically
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            When items are at their lowest price:
          </p>
          <ul class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Buy in reasonable quantities</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Consider storage space</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Track expiration dates</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Focus on frequently used items</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            7. Follow the Sales Cycles
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Most items go on sale every 6-8 weeks. Track prices to know when to expect the best deals.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            8. Join Store Loyalty Programs
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Maximize savings by:
          </p>
          <ul class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Signing up for store rewards</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Using store apps</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Loading digital coupons</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Tracking reward points</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            9. Find Multiple Coupon Sources
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Look for coupons in:
          </p>
          <ul class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Sunday newspapers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Store flyers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Manufacturer websites</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Mobile apps</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
              <span>Email newsletters</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
            10. Practice Makes Perfect
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Start small and gradually increase your couponing expertise. Keep track of your savings to stay motivated!
          </p>
        </section>

        {/* Conclusion */}
        <div class="mt-8 sm:mt-12 p-4 sm:p-8 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl">
          <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Remember, extreme couponing is a skill that takes time to master. Start small, stay organized, and gradually build your expertise. With these tips and consistent practice, you'll be well on your way to achieving significant savings on your shopping trips.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Custom styling for better visual hierarchy */
  .prose h2 {
    @apply font-display;
    scroll-margin-top: 100px;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    @apply leading-relaxed text-gray-600;
  }

  .prose ul {
    @apply my-4 sm:my-6;
  }

  .prose li {
    @apply text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base;
  }

  /* Smooth scroll behavior for anchor links */
  html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
  }

  /* Better touch targets on mobile */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .prose li {
      @apply py-1;
    }
    
    .prose a {
      @apply py-2;
    }
  }
</style>
